value.0: Alen was an officer in the Tethyrian Military, stationed in Southspire Hold of all places.
Armor and clothing of this type was produced during the Interregnum years. There was still a lot of it around.
In Tethyr, the longsword was considered a civilized weapon. This particular sword was sharp beyond belief.
These thin leather gloves are several centuries old, but due to their lasting enchantments, they still provide the wearer with greatly improved physical strength.
Wearing gloves is usually just a matter of fashion, since they do not afford any protection unless infused with magic.
This well made halberd was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
The halberd is the most common polearm, and could be called a cross between a spear and an axe.  Such weapons are often mass-produced for militia, and serve well when defending against marauders.
This well made short sword was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
One of the first types of sword to come into existence, the short sword is a double-edged weapon about two feet long.  it is an economical weapon, and a favorite of archers and rogues.

Though the notice banner that once clung to this post is now gone, it is common knowledge that Queen-Monarch Zaranda Star has declared surveys be taken across the new Tethyrian domain. This is one such survey post, meant to mark locations of importance.

This post designates a location point that can be returned to after resets from the OOC location room. Click on this post to set this location as a save point.
Ring this bell, if you dare...
These arrows boast an amount of flamable material by the arrowhead.
These finely crafted bolts bear a firey enchantment that makes them very desirable in combat.
The jambiya is a hooked dagger worn by almost all Calishite men. Calishites seem to favor curved blades in general. This jambiya was meant for someone important.
This simple golden ring is several centuries old, but due to its lasting enchantments, it still provides wearers with a measure of protection from harm as first intended.
Rings are commonly worn on the fingers as ornamentation, but some are potent magic items.
The tantan is popular with halflings and humans south of the Dalelands, but it is disliked by dwarves.

Named after a wizard from Neverwinter, haunspeir is sold as a tobacco-like paste or dried in a pill form. It is used by wizards and others who need to rapidly boast their intelligence.

Type: Ingested DC12
Initial Effect: 1d4 points of damage
Secondary Effect: 1d4 + 1 bonus to Intelligence for 1d10 + 15 minutes.
Side Effects: All slashing and peircing damage against the target gains an extra point.
Overdose: If more than 1 is taken within 24 hours, the target suffers an immediate 2d4 points of damage (no save)
Addiction: Low
Garlic is well known as a herb for flavoring foods and treating heat stroke among the preasantry. It is also used to repulse vampires.
This agate can used in Darkvision spells.

Fire agate forms in thin brown layers that refract the incoming light, giving the gem its "fire." The refraction often forms patterns reminiscent of a dragon's scales, which makes it prized by sorcerers who claim to trace their lineage back to dragonkin. A well-cut stone has its outer layers polished and ground away until only the fire is visible.
